In order to determine the EC50, varying concentrations of each extract (1–100 μg/ml) were applied to DBT cells from the adsorption period throughout the infection cycle. For all of the extracts tested, MHV production decreased in a dose-dependent manner; 50 μg/ml of Coptidis rhizoma completely abolished MHV production (Fig. 2
). The EC50 of Cimicifuga rhizoma, Meliae cortex, Coptidis rhizoma, Phellodendron cortex, and Sophora subprostrata radix were 19.4 ± 7.0, 13.0 ± 1.4, 2.0 ± 0.5, 10.4 ± 2.2, and 27.5 ± 1.1 μg/ml, respectively (Table 2
).
